curam.util.rules
Class ResultTextWrapper

java.lang.Object
  curam.util.rules.ResultTextWrapper

public class ResultTextWrapper
extends java.lang.Object

This class is a wrapper for the existing String representation of result text of the rules engine. It provides methods to get the information about the status of an individual rule execution status.

Once a developer has the decompressed result text he/she can construct an instance of this class by providing the result text to the constructor. After that the developer has to call one of the methods ResultTextWrapper.getExecutionStatus(String), ResultTextWrapper.getExecutionStatus(String, String) or ResultTextWrapper.getExecutionStatus(String, String[]).

These methods return one of the following constants:

  • ResultTextWrapper.kSucceededStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kFailedStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kNotExecutedUnkownStatus

kNotExecutedUnkownStatus

public static final java.lang.String kNotExecutedUnkownStatus
Represents the rules engine execution not executed or unknown status. This means that the rule with the specified rule ID and the specified index information has not been executed. This could also happen due to the incorrect ID or index information being specified.

Method Detail

getExecutionStatus

public java.lang.String getExecutionStatus(java.lang.String ruleId)
Get the rule execution status based on the rule ID. This method has to be called when identifying the status of a rule item which is outside of the rule list group or objective list group.

Parameters:
ruleId - the rule ID.
Returns:
the rule execution status as one of the following strings:
  • ResultTextWrapper.kSucceededStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kFailedStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kNotExecutedUnkownStatus

getExecutionStatus

public java.lang.String getExecutionStatus(java.lang.String ruleId,
                                           java.lang.String itemIndex)
Get the rule execution status based on the rule ID and description item value. This method has to be called when identifying the execution status for a rule list group, an objective list group, any rule item within a rule list group or within an objective list group. For example: getExecutionStatus("id1", "John Smith")

Parameters:
ruleId - the rule ID.
itemIndex - the description item value.
Returns:
the rule execution status as one of the following strings:
  • ResultTextWrapper.kSucceededStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kFailedStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kNotExecutedUnkownStatus

getExecutionStatus

public java.lang.String getExecutionStatus(java.lang.String ruleId,
                                           java.lang.String[] itemIndex)
Get the rule execution status based on the rule ID and description item values. This method has to be called when identifying the execution status for a rule item nested within multiple rule list groups or objective list groups.

Parameters:
ruleId - the rule ID.
itemIndex - the description item values for all the list RDOs nesting the rule item..
Returns:
the rule execution status as one of the following strings:
  • ResultTextWrapper.kSucceededStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kFailedStatus
  • ResultTextWrapper.kNotExecutedUnkownStatus
